<TITLE> Court starts trial of Lotus Kamal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 22 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Monday framed charges against former Awami League lawmaker AHM Mostafa Kamal, better known as Lotus Kamal, his wife and their two daughters for concealing wealth information and owning property beyond their income. Judge Amar Kumar Roy of Special Judge's Court-2 housed in the Sangsad Bhaban complex framed the charges. Shirin Parveen, deputy director of the Anticorruption Commission, filed the case with Gulshan Police Station on March 22. According to case details, Lotus Kamal acquired wealth by misusing power during his tenure as lawmaker. He suppressed information about Tk 2.93 crore in assets. His wife Kashmiri Kamal and daughters Kashfi Kamal and Nafisa Kamal assisted him in the mischief, the case alleged. Lotus Kamal is now behind bars but the other accused are on the run. bdnews24.com
